# Rule 6 — WordPress

ADR: `docs/adr/ADR-0003-wordpress-first.md`  
Glue: `packages/wordpress` · Entry: `openmeta.php` · Security: `packages/security`  
Docs: `docs/security/`, `docs/guides/localization.md`

OpenMeta is **WordPress-first**. Domain packages stay testable without WP; bridges **fail closed** when WP APIs are missing.

## WordPress Coding Standards

- Framework packages (`packages/*/src`) follow **PSR-12** + OpenMeta Rule 2 (PHPCS).
- **WP-facing glue** (`openmeta.php`, `packages/wordpress`, outputs that hit `wp-admin` / front) must also respect **WordPress Coding Standards** habits:
  - Prefix everything public: functions, options, CPT, rest routes, hooks → `openmeta_` / `OpenMeta\\`
  - No PHP closing tag; escape late; validate early
  - Don’t pollute the global namespace
- Prefer WP APIs (`add_action`, `register_rest_route`, `wp_enqueue_*`) **only** inside Wordpress/Security/API bridges — not inside Fields/Database cores.
- Target supported WP from project docs (e.g. 6.4+); don’t rely on removed APIs.

## Hooks (actions)

- Register via Wordpress runtime / `ActionBridge` — stable names: `openmeta_*` (e.g. `openmeta_ready`).
- Actions **react**; they must not become a second business-logic engine.
- Document new public hooks (name, args, when fired).
- Keep `openmeta.php` thin: activation/deactivation + `plugins_loaded` boot only.

## Filters

- Use filters to **modify values** at documented extension points (`openmeta_config`, menu capability, REST namespace, etc.).
- Filters are **not** authorization — never “filter away” security checks.
- Third-party-friendly: pass enough context; don’t break backward compatibility casually.

## Capability checks

- All mutations / admin screens / sensitive REST: check via **`@openmeta/security` Gate** + Permission map (WP caps underneath).
- Prefer `current_user_can` **through** Security bridges — fail closed if WP absent.
- Map OpenMeta permissions → WP capabilities in `PermissionMap`; seed roles on activate (`CapabilityRegistrar`).
- UI hide ≠ security. Always enforce server-side.

## Escaping

- Escape **on output** (late): `Escaper::html`, `attr`, `url`, or WP `esc_html` / `esc_attr` / `esc_url` in pure WP callbacks.
- Never print raw request/storage data into admin HTML, attributes, or JS.
- Field/Admin/UI render paths must go through Security escaping helpers.

## Nonces

- State-changing requests (admin forms, builder save, settings): **Nonce create + check** via `@openmeta/security` Nonce (HMAC in CI; WP nonce handler when available).
- Nonces ≠ authentication or capability checks — use **all three** where needed.
- Fail closed on invalid/missing nonce; don’t “log and continue.”

## Translation (i18n)

- Text domain: **`openmeta`** (matches plugin header).
- User-facing strings in WP UI: `__()`, `_e()`, `esc_html__()`, `_x()` / `_n()` as appropriate — **after** load_plugin_textdomain / just-in-time i18n.
- Do not concatenate HTML inside translatable strings; use placeholders (`sprintf` + translators comments).
- Framework-internal log/exception messages for developers may stay English; anything shown to site admins/users should be translatable.

## Plugin compatibility

- Integrate through **public WP APIs** and OpenMeta hooks/filters — no core hacks, no rewriting other plugins’ internals.
- Assume other plugins exist: unique prefixes, no generic function names, no unconditional takeover of global admin menus.
- REST under `openmeta/v1` (or filtered namespace); don’t collide with other plugins’ routes.
- Gutenberg: register block metadata via bridges; don’t fork the field engine inside blocks.
- Multisite / capability differences: fail closed; don’t assume `administrator` alone forever.
- Soft-depend on optional plugins (Woo, etc.) behind `class_exists` / feature flags when added later — never hard-fatal if absent.

## Must not

- ❌ Multi-CMS abstractions  
- ❌ Domain engines inside `openmeta.php`  
- ❌ `$wpdb` schema ownership outside `database`  
- ❌ Trusting Canvas/UI without Gate + Nonce + Validation  
- ❌ Unescaped echo in admin/REST HTML  

## Tests

- CI: `ArrayWordPressRuntime` (or fakes); Native runtime no-ops safely without WP.
- Cover fail-closed caps/nonces/auth bridges.
